cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.DC

This paper is about PyTorch, a deep learning library, and its architecture and performance. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses hardware accelerators such as GPUs, which suggests cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper emphasizes the pragmatic implementation of key components, which could fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
